28/10/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- The second review meeting of the Ohrid Process for Border Management and Security was held Wednesday (27 October) in Tirana. 
The Ohrid Border Process is a joint initiative of the Western Balkan countries, the OSCE, the EU, NATO and the Stability Pact, aimed at addressing the sensitive issue of border safety. 
The five partner countries in the process are Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Croatia, Serbia-Montenegro and Macedonia. 
Talks focused on liberalisation and harmonisation of visa regimes, the fight against organised crime and trafficking, and facilitating the movement of goods, capital and people. 
(Albanian Daily News - 28/10/04; ATA - 27/10/04)
